5.27. Draw $A K \| B D$ and $D K|| A B$ (Fig. 5.17). Then $\overline{A K}=\overline{B D}, \overline{D K}=\overline{B A}$. Using the obvious equalities $\overline{A B}+\overline{B D}=\overline{A D}$, $\overline{A C}-\overline{A B}=\overline{B C}$; adding them term by term, we get

$$
\overline{A C}+\overline{B D}=\overline{A D}+\overline{B C}
$$

![](https://cdn.mathpix.com/cropped/2024_05_21_1e3d8d2f6605ac23e2a5g-612.jpg?height=371&width=241&top_left_y=676&top_left_x=868)

Next, using Fig. 5.17, we write

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \overline{M N}=\overline{M B}+\overline{B C}+\overline{C N}=\frac{1}{2} \overline{A B}+\overline{B C}+\frac{1}{2} \overline{C D} \\
& \overline{M N}=\overline{M A}+\overline{A D}+\overline{D N}=\frac{1}{2} \overline{B A}+\overline{A D}+\frac{1}{2} \overline{D C}
\end{aligned}
$$

Adding these equalities: $\quad 2 \overline{M N}=\overline{B C}+\overline{A D}$, or $\overline{M N}=\frac{1}{2}(\overline{B C}+\overline{A D})$, from which, by (1), we have $\overline{M N}=\frac{1}{2}(\overline{A C}+\overline{B D})$. Now using the inequality $|\bar{a}+\bar{b}| \leq|\vec{a}|+|\vec{b}|$ and finally we get $M N \leq \frac{1}{2}(B C+A D), M N \leq \frac{1}{2}(A C+B D)$.

Solution.

Let $x$ be the number of parts processed by the first machine, and $x-n$ be the number of parts processed by the second machine. The time spent on processing one part on the first machine is $\frac{a}{x}$ hours, and on the second machine it is $-\frac{a}{x-n}$ hours. According to the condition, $\frac{a}{x-n}=\frac{a}{x}+\frac{b}{60}$, from which we get

\[
\begin{aligned}
& x=\frac{b n+\sqrt{b^{2} n^{2}+240 a b n}}{2 b} ; x-n=\frac{-b n+\sqrt{b^{2} n^{2}+240 a b n}}{2 b} \\
& \text { Answer: } \frac{b n+\sqrt{b^{2} n^{2}+240 a b n}}{2 b} \text { and } \frac{-b n+\sqrt{b^{2} n^{2}+240 a b n}}{2 b} \text { parts. }
\end{aligned}
\]
